Record.CAVI-Subject:
Int.: Athena pouring a libation for a seated Heracles. A: three youths on
winged chariots{3}. B: Zeus and Hera enthroned; goddess behind a throne (Iris?);
goddess by an altar holding up a wreath to crown a male (Heracles?); palm tree;
three goddesses.

Int.: Hermes at an altar. A: gods and goddesses on Olympus (Zeus, Hera,
Ganymede; Poseideon and Amphitrite; Dionysus). B: Achilles and Hector fighting;
at left, Athena and Thetis.

Record.CAVI-Footnotes:
{1} Late (Beazley, ARV[1] 728/53), but R. Guy's combination of the frs. shows
that the vase is early. {2} satyr and maenad, maenad (Beazley). {3} so L.-H.;
not in K.-D. Could it be Σ[ιμος](?). Three-stroke sigma.
